This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump during a meeting with various supporters and representatives from different organizations. The main focus of the conversation is the nomination of Judge Gorsuch for the United States Supreme Court. President Trump praises Gorsuch's qualifications and expresses his desire for a dignified and efficient confirmation process. He also criticizes Democrats who plan to oppose Gorsuch's nomination, stating that it would be dishonest considering he received unanimous endorsement in 2006. Additionally, President Trump suggests that Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell should invoke the "nuclear option" to bypass any potential gridlock in the confirmation process.